      "errorMessage": "task_id: ses_361bd1f67ffeFedapbJTlL7o4m (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is a complete summary of everything in the `spec/` directory.\n\n---\n\n## Directory Tree Structure\n\n```\nspec/\n├── README.md\n├── CONVENTIONS.md\n├── module-catalog.md\n├── architecture/\n│   ├── overview.md\n│   └── runtime-lifecycle.md\n├── behavior/\n│   ├── configuration.md\n│   ├── error-handling.md\n│   ├── persistence-and-io.md\n│   └── state-model.md\n├── workflows/\n│   └── core-workflows.md\n└── modules/\n    ├── cli/\n    │   └── index.md\n    ├── engine/\n    │   └── engine.md\n    ├── integrations/\n    │   ├── beads.md\n    │   ├── interactive.md\n    │   └── opencode.md\n    ├── infrastructure/\n    │   ├── config.md\n    │   ├── events.md\n    │   ├── init.md\n    │   ├── output-parser.md\n    │   ├── progress.md\n    │   ├── run-state.md\n    │   ├── run-status.md\n    │   ├── skills.md\n    │   ├── template.md\n    │   ├── timeout.md\n    │   └── types.md\n    └── phases/\n        ├── decompose.md\n        ├── forward.md\n        └── reverse.md\n```\n\n**Total: 29 files across 9 directories.**\n\n---\n\n## Full Contents: spec/README.md\n\n```\n# Spec Directory\n\nThis directory contains reverse-engineered specifications for the super-ralph\nagent framework. All documents are produced by reading observable behavior,\nsource code, and runtime artifacts — not from internal design documents or\nauthor interviews.\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe `spec/` tree provides a clean-room description of how super-ralph works so that:\n- Contributors can understand module contracts without reading all source code.\n- The forward phase can use these docs as authoritative context when implementing beads.\n- Reviewers have a stable reference for verifying that behavior matches intent.\n\n## Scope\n\nCovers: Engine, Phases, Subsystems (config, beads, opencode, templates, run-state, output-parsing), CLI.\nOut of scope: internal opencode SDK, beads-rust internals, third-party tooling not imported by this project.\n\n## Navigation\n\nRead in this order for top-down understanding:\n1. CONVENTIONS.md — writing rules, clean-room constraints, confidence labels, module doc template.\n2. Module specs (one file per major source module).\n\n## Artifact Table\n\n| Artifact | Path | Status | Covers |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Writing conventions | CONVENTIONS.md | stable | Meta |\n| Engine loop | (pending) | draft | src/engine.ts |\n| Forward phase | (pending) | draft | src/forward.ts |\n| Reverse phase | (pending) | draft | src/reverse.ts |\n| Decompose phase | (pending) | draft | src/decompose.ts |\n| config loading | (pending) | draft | src/config.ts |\n| bead integration | (pending) | draft | src/beads.ts |\n| opencode adapter | (pending) | draft | src/opencode.ts |\n| Template resolution | (pending) | draft | src/template.ts |\n| Run-state persistence | (pending) | draft | src/run-state.ts |\n| Output parsing | (pending) | draft | src/output-parser.ts |\n| CLI entry point | (pending) | draft | src/index.ts |\n```\n\nNote: The README artifact table lists items as \"pending/draft\" — this is outdated relative to the actual directory content, where detailed module specs do in fact exist.\n\n---\n\n## Full Contents: spec/module-catalog.md\n\n```\n# Module Catalog\n\nComplete inventory of all source modules in the super-ralph agent framework, grouped by domain.\nSource examined at commit: ecc95c0 (2026-02-27)\n\n## Coverage Key\n- covered: A detailed spec file exists in spec/.\n- partial: Spec exists but is incomplete or draft.\n- todo: No spec file yet.\n\n## Domains (19 source modules in src/, five domains):\n\n1. Phases — Top-level command orchestration (3 modules)\n   - Forward      src/forward.ts    todo\n   - Decompose    src/decompose.ts  todo\n   - Reverse      src/reverse.ts    todo\n\n2. Engine — Core iteration loop and lifecycle (1 module)\n   - Engine       src/engine.ts     todo\n\n3. Integrations — External service adapters (3 modules)\n   - opencode adapter    src/opencode.ts     todo\n   - Interactive session src/interactive.ts  todo\n   - bead integration    src/beads.ts        todo\n\n4. Infrastructure — Cross-cutting support utilities (9 modules)\n   - Types        src/types.ts          todo\n   - config       src/config.ts         todo\n   - Template     src/template.ts       todo\n   - Output parser src/output-parser.ts todo\n   - Run state    src/run-state.ts      todo\n   - Run status   src/run-status.ts     todo\n   - Progress     src/progress.ts       todo\n   - Skills       src/skills.ts         todo\n   - Timeout      src/timeout.ts        todo\n   - Init         src/init.ts           todo\n   - Events       src/events.ts         todo\n\n5. CLI Entry Point (1 module)\n   - Index        src/index.ts          todo\n\n## Detailed Spec Files\nNo detailed module spec files exist yet. All entries above are `todo`.\n```\n\nNote: This catalog lists all statuses as `todo`, which is also outdated — the `spec/modules/` subtree contains detailed spec files for every module listed.\n\n---\n\n## All Other Spec Files: Names, Sizes, and Purposes\n\n### Meta / Top-Level\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `CONVENTIONS.md` | 135 | Defines the rules for all spec documents: clean-room constraints, confidence labels (`[CONFIRMED]`, `[INFERRED]`, `[ASSUMED]`, `[UNKNOWN]`), shared terminology glossary (bead, epic, iteration, phase, run, session, skill, template), the required section template every module spec must follow, and Markdown style + file-naming rules. |\n\n### Architecture\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `architecture/overview.md` | 219 | High-level description of the 5 domains and all 19 modules, cross-domain interaction boundaries (CLI→Phase→Engine→opencode adapter→br CLI), the project filesystem layout after `init`, and configuration boundary. Includes ASCII sequence diagrams. |\n| `architecture/runtime-lifecycle.md` | 287 | Step-by-step walkthrough of the 3 lifecycle stages (initialization, steady-state loop, shutdown) with source-cited line references, a full sequence diagram for a single forward-phase iteration, all timeout mechanisms, and the separate `init` lifecycle. |\n\n### Behavior\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `behavior/configuration.md` | 179 | Configuration sources and precedence (CLI flags > config.toml > hard-coded defaults), merge semantics, the full default values table, model resolution 3-tier lookup, validation behavior, the one environment variable (`SUPER_RALPH_DEBUG`), and config lifetime/scope. |\n| `behavior/error-handling.md` | 417 | Complete error taxonomy (`CompletionResult.status`, `SessionState.status`, `BeadInfo.status`), the 3 failure strategies (retry/skip/abort) with detailed mechanics, the 2 timeout mechanisms (hard wall-clock + inactivity watchdog), all thrown errors by component, and 7 per-workflow negative-path scenarios with observable outcomes. |\n| `behavior/persistence-and-io.md` | 281 | All filesystem read/write boundaries (organized by trigger point), all network I/O via the opencode SDK, all child process invocations (full `br` command table), standard stream usage (stdout/stderr/stdin), process exit codes, and I/O ordering guarantees. |\n| `behavior/state-model.md` | 263 | In-process transient state (SessionState counters, engine loop counters, IterationResult fields, StreamCapture buffers, ServerHandle), on-disk persistent state (session.json, events.jsonl, iteration transcripts, progress.md), and external state (BeadInfo owned by br CLI, opencode session state). |\n\n### Workflows\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `workflows/core-workflows.md` | 594 | End-to-end behavioral specs for all 7 user-visible workflows: WF-01 init, WF-02 reverse (3 modes), WF-03 decompose, WF-04 forward (4 alternate flows), WF-05 status, WF-06 doctor, WF-07 task_complete tool. Each includes participating modules, trigger, preconditions, normal flow, failure outcomes, and observable outputs/state changes. |\n\n### Module Specs — CLI\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `modules/cli/index.md` | 95 | Full module spec for `src/index.ts`: argument parsing, all CLI flags with types, exit code handling, JSON output file writing, all dispatched subcommands. |\n\n### Module Specs — Engine\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `modules/engine/engine.md` | 89 | Full module spec for `src/engine.ts`: inputs/outputs, the select-prompt-execute-evaluate loop, retry/skip/abort strategy, event emission, run tracker side effects, dry-run mode. |\n\n### Module Specs — Phases\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `modules/phases/decompose.md` | 74 | Module spec for `src/decompose.ts`: epic creation, per-iteration bead production, reading spec file per iteration, fetching existing beads, optional review/bugscan/audit beads, 50-iteration default max. |\n| `modules/phases/forward.md` | 74 | Module spec for `src/forward.ts`: bead-selection strategy, hybrid priority ordering, per-iteration ready-bead fetch, model resolution by area label, progress injection, `maxIterations = beadCount * 2` heuristic. |\n| `modules/phases/reverse.md` | 89 | Module spec for `src/reverse.ts`: 2 modes (interactive with `@clack/prompts` Q&A; autonomous loop), skill loading, spec file refinement on iterations > 1, mock answers support, direct RunTracker management in interactive mode. |\n\n### Module Specs — Integrations\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `modules/integrations/beads.md` | 80 | Module spec for `src/beads.ts`: all 6 public functions (`getAllReady`, `getBeadDetails`, `closeBead`, `getAllBeads`, `getEpicProgress`, `runBr`), subprocess spawning via `Bun.spawn`, JSON output parsing, error on non-zero exit. |\n| `modules/integrations/interactive.md` | 84 | Module spec for `src/interactive.ts`: SSE event subscription, `question.asked` interception, `@clack/prompts` rendering, mock answer replay, singleton module state, Q&A log accumulation. |\n| `modules/integrations/opencode.md` | 86 | Module spec for `src/opencode.ts`: server lifecycle (`startServer`/`connectToServer`), session creation, SSE streaming, inactivity watchdog, `task_complete` extraction, broken symlink repair, v1/v2 SDK usage. |\n\n### Module Specs — Infrastructure\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `modules/infrastructure/config.md` | 74 | Module spec for `src/config.ts`: `loadConfig` (TOML read + shallow merge), `resolveModel` (3-tier lookup), failure on malformed model string, silent fallback to defaults if file absent. |\n| `modules/infrastructure/events.md` | 67 | Module spec for `src/events.ts`: `EngineEventEmitter` (lightweight pub/sub), `attachDefaultConsoleRenderer`, synchronous dispatch, unsubscribe function pattern, 12-event discriminated union. |\n| `modules/infrastructure/init.md` | 79 | Module spec for `src/init.ts`: 9-step idempotent scaffolding sequence, template copying (skip-if-exists), opencode plugin installation, `br init` invocation, AGENTS.md creation/append. |\n| `modules/infrastructure/output-parser.md` | 64 | Module spec for `src/output-parser.ts`: `StreamCapture` dual-buffer (raw SSE lines + display text), 250,000-character cap per stream with truncation marker, `toolStatusText` formatting, no I/O side effects. |\n| `modules/infrastructure/progress.md` | 70 | Module spec for `src/progress.ts`: `appendProgress` (one Markdown block per iteration), `readRecentProgress` (returns last N blocks for prompt injection), `formatProgressEntry` utility. |\n| `modules/infrastructure/run-state.md` | 83 | Module spec for `src/run-state.ts`: `RunTracker` factory, run directory creation, `session.json` overwrite on every event, `events.jsonl` append-only log, per-iteration transcript files. |\n| `modules/infrastructure/run-status.md` | 65 | Module spec for `src/run-status.ts`: `getRunStatus` resolving by explicit ID or `\"latest\"`, reads session.json + event count + transcript listing, all read-only. |\n| `modules/infrastructure/skills.md` | 65 | Module spec for `src/skills.ts`: `loadSkill` (name→file or path→file), 4 built-in skill names (`feature`, `bug`, `hotfix`, `refactor`), `getCliDir` for CLI asset location. |\n| `modules/infrastructure/template.md` | 69 | Module spec for `src/template.ts`: `loadTemplate` (reads + compiles `.hbs`), `renderPrompt` (renders with variable context), Handlebars dependency, missing-template error with `init` hint. |\n| `modules/infrastructure/timeout.md` | 60 | Module spec for `src/timeout.ts`: `withTimeout(task, ms, message)` promise race, timer cleanup in `finally`, no cancellation signal sent to the underlying task. |\n| `modules/infrastructure/types.md` | 49 | Module spec for `src/types.ts`: purely a declaration file, no runtime logic. Documents that it is the single source of truth for all shared interfaces (`BeadInfo`, `LoopConfig`, `IterationResult`, `CompletionResult`, `PhaseFlags`, etc.), with no imports of its own. |\n\n---\n\n## Key Observations\n\n1. **The module-catalog.md is outdated**: It lists all 19 modules as `todo` (no spec written), but detailed spec files now exist for all 19 modules in `spec/modules/`.\n\n2. **The README.md artifact table is also outdated**: It marks all module specs as \"pending/draft\", but they are in fact fully written.\n\n3. **Source examined at commit `ecc95c0` (2026-02-27)**: All spec files were produced from the same snapshot.\n\n4. **The spec is fully reverse-engineered**: Every file rigorously cites source locations, uses confidence labels (`[CONFIRMED]`, `[INFERRED]`, `[ASSUMED]`, `[UNKNOWN]`), and maintains a clean-room posture per the CONVENTIONS.md rules.\n\n5. **The 7-workflow document** (`workflows/core-workflows.md`, 594 lines) is by far the largest file and serves as the primary behavioral reference for operators.\n</task_result>",
